<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1347">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/123.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that his Government is
                                sending Secretary of Legation at Habana, Mr. Cardenas, to El Paso
                                arriving there evening 17th instant to learn condition and render
                                assistance to suffering Spaniards at Chihuahua. Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs wishes that Cardenas may communicate direct and cooperate
                                with our Consuls there and elsewhere. Please advise me.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>